.START 

Sun Co. said it will begin a market trial Nov. 1 of a reformulated diesel fuel developed to meet tightening standards on auto and truck emissions. 

The refining and marketing company said it will carry out the trial mostly at selected Sunoco service stations in the Philadelphia area.
The company added that it will do research on methanol-gasoline blends in cooperation with Ford Motor Co. and on reformulated gasoline at its own automotive lab. 

